	    ,{"code":"SI", "dict":"DETECTOR", "idict":22,"hlp":"Silicon detector"}]
	,"x4freetext":[" Charged particles were detected using"
		,"Silicon Highly-segmented Array for Reactions and"
		,"Coulex (SHARC). The whole array consisted of"
		,"downstream end cap detector covering angles 7-27deg,"
		,"downstream box detector covering polar angles 32-71"
		,"deg, upstream box detector covering polar angles"
		,"103-145 deg and partial upstream end cup detector"
		,"covering polar angles 148-172 deg. Each detector"
		,"consisted of four dE-E telescopes made of double"
		,"sided silicon strip detectors of various thicknesses,"
		,"backed with thick E detector. Total solid angle"
		,"coverage was almost 2Pi."]
	}
	,{"x4pointer":" "
	,"x4codes":[{"code":"HPGE", "dict":"DETECTOR", "idict":22,"hlp":"Hyperpure Germanium detector"}]
	,"x4freetext":[" Gamma rays were detected by TIGRESS array"
		,"consisting of eleven clover detectors. The coincidences"
		,"with SHARC array was achieved, but because of low"
		,"statistics gamma ray data were not used."]
	}
      ]
